    <div style="text-align:center">
        <h1>What to do Before and After Your Donation?</h1><br />
        <div>
            <h2>Before Blood Donation</h2>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Eat Iron-Rich Foods</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Eat iron-rich foods, such as red meat, fish, poultry, beans, spinach, iron-fortified cereals or raisins</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Be Well Rested and Hydrate</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Get a good night's sleep the night before your donation, eat healthy foods and drink extra liquids</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Have a good meal</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Have a good meal at least 3 hours before blood donation.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Avoid smoking</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Avoid smoking on the day donating. You can smoke 3 hours after donation.</i></p>
            <p style="text-align:left"><b>Avoid alcohol</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> You will not be eligible to donate blood if you have consumed alcohol 24 hours before donation.</i></p>
         </div><br />
         
         <div>
            <h2>After Blood Donation</h2>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Enjoy a Snack</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Relax for a few minutes in our refreshment & recovery area - have some cookies or other snacks - you've earned it!</i></p>
              <p style="text-align:left"><b>Drink Extra Liquids</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Drink an extra four glasses of liquids and avoid alcohol over the next 24 hours.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Leave hospital after 15 minutes</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> After donation you sit in an observation area, where you rest and eat a light snack. After 15 minuites, you can leave.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>If you feel lightheaded,</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Lie down with your feet up until the feeling passes.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"<b>If you have bleeding after removing the bandage,</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Put pressure on the site and rise your arm until the bleeding stops.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>If bleeding or brusing occurs under the skin,</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Apply a cold pack to the area periodically during the first 24 hours.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>If your arm is sore,</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> Take a pain reliever such as acetaminophen(Tylenol, others). Avoid taking aspirin or ibuprofen(Advil, Motrin IB, others) for the first 24 to 48 hours after donation.</i></p>
             <p style="text-align:left"><b>Tell Others About Your Good Deed</b><br /><br /><i style="color:#000000"> The gratification of giving blood is a feeling you'll want to share.</i></p>
        </div>

    </div>
    
